那么我们来聊聊这些遍布世界各地的有趣地方吧。

33
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:38,520
Now on Language Takeaway.
现在是“语言要点”环节。

34
00:01:38,520 --> 00:01:41,360
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

35
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:45,800
So the set phrase for this, Marco, is the seven wonders of the world.
Marco，这个固定短语是“世界七大奇迹”。

36
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:47,600
Now the key here is the word wonder.
这里的关键词是“奇迹”。

37
00:01:47,600 --> 00:01:48,600
What is a wonder?
什么是奇迹？

38
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:49,600
Right.
对。

39
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:54,240
A wonder is something very amazing, incredible.
奇迹是非常惊人、不可思议的东西。

40
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:57,400
It's something that's beyond your imagination almost.
它几乎超乎你的想象。

41
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:58,400
That's right.
没错。

42
00:01:58,400 --> 00:02:02,960
You can't even imagine how man or how someone created it.
你甚至无法想象人类是如何建造出它的。

43
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:08,200
And so wonderful is a similar word that's an adjective, something that's just great,
而“wonderful”是一个类似的形容词，意思是极好的、

44
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:10,080
fantastic is wonderful.
美妙的。

45
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:12,320
A wonder is something very, very special.
奇迹是非常非常特别的东西。

46
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:14,720
And here we have seven of them.
而这里我们有七个。

47
00:02:14,720 --> 00:02:15,720
That's right.
没错。

48
